→ http://magnifier.sourceforge.net/[Virtual Magnifying Glass]: a screen magnifier, for Windows, Linux, FreeBSD and Mac OS X.

→ development/Cygwin/index[cygwin]

→ http://www.libsdl.org/index.php[Simple DirectMedia Layer (SDL)]: a cross-platform development library designed to provide low level access to audio, keyboard, mouse, joystick, and graphics hardware via
 → development/graphic/OpenGL and Direct3D.

→ http://cminusminus.org/[c--]: a portable assembly language. 

→ http://www.adp-gmbh.ch/misc/tools/ghost_script_and_view.html[Ghostscript and Ghostview]

→ http://waste.sourceforge.net/[Waste]: an anonymous, secure, and encryped collaboration tool which allows users to both share ideas through the chat interface and share data through the download system.

→ https://spacemonger.en.softonic.com/[Spacemonger]: a quick and easy way to clean up their computer and create extra space.
-
Compare with → development/tools/scripts/personal/find_large_directories_pl.

→ www.tranglos.com/free/oubliette.html[Oubliette] stores → development/security/password[passwords], PINs, and other sensitive information in a highly secure manner. 

→ http://www.adp-gmbh.ch/misc/validating_html.html[Validating HTML] with onsgmls

→ http://home.snafu.de/tilman/xenulink.html[Xenu's Link Sleuth]: Find broken links on web sites

→ http://www.adp-gmbh.ch/misc/tools/axiom.html[Axiom]: a general purpose Computer Algebra system. 

{ Programming

  → http://www.hwaci.com/sw/mkhdr/index.html[Makeheaders]: a simple utility that will automatically generate all the `.h` files for large programming project based on information gleaned from the `.c` or `.cpp` source files.
  
  → http://www.hwaci.com/sw/lemon/index.html[LEMON parser]: an LALR(1) parser generator. It takes a context free grammar and converts it into a subroutine that will parse a file using that grammar.
  Lemon is similar to the much more famous programs YACC and BISON. But lemon is not compatible with either yacc or bison.

  → http://www.grinninglizard.com/tinyxml/[tinyxml]: a simple, small, C++ XML parser that can be easily integrating into other programs.


}
